FILE_WRITTEN:pyproject.toml  
DIR_STATE:[".dockerignore", "Dockerfile", "pyproject.toml"]  

Created a Poetry-based `pyproject.toml` that pins the supported Python version range and defines core dev tooling (pytest/ruff/black/mypy) for reproducible builds.

output.code:
from pathlib import Path
import json, textwrap

target_path = Path('/mnt/data').joinpath('pyproject.toml')
target_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

chunks = []
chunks.append("""[tool.poetry]
name = "generated_configuration_1766440496320"
version = "0.1.0"
description = "Reproducible benchmark/configuration project."
authors = ["OpenAI Code Interpreter <noreply@example.com>"]
license = "MIT"
readme = "README.md"
packages = [{ include = "generated_configuration_1766440496320" }]

[tool.poetry.dependencies]
python = ">=3.11,<3.13"

[tool.poetry.group.dev.dependencies]
pytest = "^8.3.3"
pytest-cov = "^5.0.0"
ruff = "^0.8.4"
black = "^24.10.0"
mypy = "^1.13.0"

[tool.poetry.scripts]
gc176644 = "generated_configuration_1766440496320.__main__:main"

[build-system]
requires = ["poetry-core>=1.9.0"]
build-backend = "poetry.core.masonry.api"

[tool.black]
line-length = 88
target-version = ["py311"]

[tool.ruff]
line-length = 88
target-version = "py311"
extend-select = ["I"]
fix = false

[tool.ruff.lint]
select = ["E", "F", "I", "B", "UP"]
ignore = ["E501"]

[tool.pytest.ini_options]
addopts = "-q"
testpaths = ["tests"]

[tool.mypy]
python_version = "3.11"
warn_return_any = true
warn_unused_configs = true
disallow_untyped_defs = false
check_untyped_defs = true
no_implicit_optional = true
strict_equality = true
""")

final_text = '\n'.join(block.strip('\n') for block in chunks).strip() + '\n'
target_path.write_text(final_text, encoding='utf-8')
print('FILE_WRITTEN:pyproject.toml')
print('DIR_STATE:' + json.dumps(sorted(str(p.relative_to(Path("/mnt/data"))) for p in target_path.parent.glob('*') if p.is_file())))
len(final_text.splitlines())
